text:
=AI Call Recap=

Knowledge Graphs & Domain Expertise
The group dove into how to create structured, interconnected â€œknowledge graphsâ€ from unstructured sources (e.g. PDFs). They discussed using LLMs to infer domain-specific rules/ontologies and how these graphs can enable more precise reasoning and better retrieval-augmented generation.

Personal â€œDigital Twinsâ€ & Identity
Several participants want an agent that deeply understands their personal goals and contextâ€”like a â€œdigital twinâ€â€”to handle tasks from self-reflection and accountability to practical daily workflows (e.g. scheduling, posting, outreach).

Multi-Agent Workflows & Orchestration
They explored ideas around â€œapprentice agentsâ€ for capturing an expertâ€™s knowledge, then repurposing it for broader audiences or specialized tasks. This includes building hierarchical systems where a â€œmanagerâ€ agent delegates subtasks to domain-specific â€œchildâ€ agents.
